  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QS/PROCUREMENT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare cost estimates, quotations, and bills of quantities (BOQ).</li>\n  <li>Source, evaluate, and negotiate with suppliers and subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>Issue purchase orders and track material deliveries.</li>\n  <li>Prepare progress claims, variation orders, and final accounts.</li>\n  <li>Assist Project Manager in project cost control and budgeting.</li>\n  <li>Maintain good relationships with vendors and ensure timely procurement.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Quantity Surveying, Building, or related field.</li>\n  <li>1–3 years’ relevant experience in construction or fit-out projects <em>(fresh grads may apply)</em>.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of procurement, costing, and construction materials.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office (Excel, Word).</li>\n  <li>Good communication and negotiation skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and handle multiple tasks.</li>\n</ul>",
